  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Re-strengthen base for good business performance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Unfortunately to say, but Ndumberi has to make a step back. 2014 was supposed to be the year to elaborate a business plan and to prepare to make a - huge - step forward in 2015, by starting first steps of own processing plant. But due to governance issues - and therefore related issues on financial management and lower performance in business, this was not achieved. Ndumberi needs to re-strengthen its base for good business performance.

Due to the above-mentioned issues, in action plan for 2015 focus is on strengthening Ndumberi&apos;s governance and financial management. Implementation of business plan will be put on hold until milk volumes are back to 18,000 liters. Focus will only be on marketing of yoghurt.

Activities in action plan:

Develop a feed production and sales plan 
done through support of SNV

Business plan
-	On hold

ICT
-	Update website www.ndumberidairy.com 

Performance management
-	Training of Board members on a) role of Board (strategy, effective controls) and management (daily operations, prepare investment proposals), b) develop practical procurement policies (in accordance with Public Procurement Oversight Authority), c) strategic development, d) HR
-	Develop Strategic Plan 2015 &#x2013; 2018 (combined with training, practical, short)
-	Training of Staff on a) supervisory skills for departmental heads , b) team cohesiveness, and c) a bit of governance and financial management
-	Refresher course milk graders, member care, and ethics is on SNV&#x2019;s action plan.

-	Working capital loan from K-unity

-	Follow-up on the Software integration

Yoghurt
-	In 2015 Ndumberi will only concentrate on yoghurt
-	Elaborate marketing plan for yoghurt (hire marketing agency)
-	Market research yoghurt sales Kiambu and Nairobi
-	Stakeholder forum once a quarter

Milk
-	Only produce pasteurised milk if profitable and on demand

Restructure finance, make yoghurt into profitable business, improve governance, make realistic strategy plan and start immediately carrying it out.</narrative>
  </description>
